author: Inside Edition
description: The last time Nicole Kidman and Keith Urban were spotted together in public was three months ago at the FIFA Club World Cup in Nashville. Five days later, Kidman celebrated their 19 years of marriage with a photo posted on social media. Urban reportedly moved out of their home at the beginning of this summer and has his own place in Nashville. There are also reports that Kidman did not want this separation.
title: Were There Clues Leading To Nicole Kidman And Keith Urban's Split?

author: Inside Edition
description: There's a new celebrity in Hollywood and her name is Tilly Norwood. Tilly is already causing major controversy because she is not real. She's AI-generated. Tilly is the creation of a Dutch comedian who says "multiple talent agents have shown interest in signing the AI actress." AI protection was a key sticking point during the writer and actors strikes in 2023. Now, their fears seem to be coming true.
title: Hollywood's Newest Actress Is AI-Generated

author: Inside Edition
description: There's a promising new upstart on the college football field. Tom Sillow is starting his college football career at the age of 58. Sillow is a defensive lineman with the Lycoming College Warriors in Williamsport, Pennsylvania. Inside Edition's Emma Keady checked out his moves at a recent practice. A lifelong weightlifter in excellent physical shape, Sillow always wanted to play college football but never got the chance to as a youngster.
title: Newest Player On This College Football Team Is 58 Years Old

author: Inside Edition
description: Robert Springsteen was wrongly convicted in the Yogurt Shop Murders. He was sentenced to death for the slaying of four teens in a yogurt shop in Austin, Texas, in 1991. His conviction was overturned in 2006. Police announced Monday that the real killer was Robert Eugene Brashers based on new DNA evidence. Brashers killed himself during a shootout with police in 1999. Springsteen was freed after he had served eight years in prison and is featured in the HBO docu-series "The Yogurt Shop Murders."
title: Man Freed After Death Sentence in Yogurt Shop Murder Case Speaks Out

author: Inside Edition
description: In a bizarre medical mystery, one of Caroline Miele's shoulders has become higher than the other. The 28-year-old professional dancer is desperate to find out why. Her doctors said there was no structural issue that would explain her condition. Miele began posting TikTok videos about her condition and was inundated with advice, including some from doctors, but so far nothing has worked.
title: Woman Looks For Answers To Her Bizarre Medical Mystery

author: Inside Edition
description: President Donald Trump appeared taken aback Tuesday when he walked into a room full of top military brass. The generals stood at attention, expressionless. When the president started speaking, they sat with their hands on their laps. Secretary of Defense Pete Hegseth's speech drew fire. He spoke about overweight recruits. The military gathering, which cost $6 million, was criticized as "pointless" and "wasteful."
title: Trump's $6 Million Military Gathering Criticized As 'Pointless'

author: Inside Edition
description: It was a traffic stop that just kept getting stranger. The Fairview Heights Police in Illinois posted bodycam of the odd incident on Facebook. An officer was not in his vehicle when it was struck from behind on the side of a road. The driver who hit the officer's car, Keajion Jennings, 28, was quite forthcoming, claiming he had been drinking and using weed. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Suspect Says He Rear-Ended Cop Car Out Of Boredom In Illinois

author: Inside Edition
description: After Lorenz Kraus’ parents disappeared eight years ago, their social security benefits were still being collected, prompting police to obtain a search warrant. Their remains were found in their backyard, and Kraus reached out to CBS affiliate WRGB-TV, sitting down for an on-air interview to describe the 2017 killings.
title: Man Confesses To Killing His Parents In TV Interview #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A man wasn't afraid of horses, until a mounted officer claimed his horse could smell narcotics. That's when the man took off running. One of the officers told local media he thought the suspect was playing along as part of the joke, but when he wouldn't stop running, they realized he was actually fleeing. It was not surprising that the man who seemed to believe a horse could sniff out narcotics also believed he could outrun a horse. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Man Runs After Mounted Police Officer Jokes About 'Narcotics-Smelling Horse'

title: What's The Controversy Behind 'Swiped' Movie? #shorts
